# Workspace Sync LLM Guide

## Purpose

Use this command group to create or refresh the project-local contract that agents read before operating in a repository.

## When To Run

- Run init when a repository does not yet have a local contract.
- Run update when packaged shared guidance should be refreshed.
- Run update after upgrading the CLI package.

## How To Read The Result

- Created entries are newly written contract assets.
- Updated entries are packaged shared assets refreshed from the current CLI version.
- Preserved entries are local assets kept intact.
- Validation errors mean a generated contract asset failed before it was written.

## Examples

- If init creates the contract, read it before editing project code.
- If update preserves local assets, treat that as intentional user-owned knowledge.
- If update changes shared guidance, rerun relevant checks before making architecture edits.
- If a local rule conflicts with refreshed shared guidance, ask which project-specific decision should win.

## Agent Tips

- Do not overwrite local rule decisions just to refresh shared guidance.
- After sync, read the contract before editing application code.
- If sync reports preserved local assets, treat them as user-owned project knowledge.
- Run architecture checks after sync when architecture rules changed.
